text:
@Kristina Azovtseva

- spoken English OK, a bit worse than Michael's, better than Artem's - understood everything I said but was at a loss for words occasionally; decent pronounciation
- wants to have experience practicing English, especially spoken
- not much work experience: teaching English and data entry
- plans to continue working with English language students on the side
- ABBYY - remote job; project is over and there is no fixed schedule, so she didn't leave this position as such but can basically choose not to continue

- thinks she can be good at sales due to good comms skills;  likes communicating - both spoken and written; says her written English is better than spoken but is keen to improve the latter
- about showing iniative: worked at fifa world cup, ticket staff - had problematic clients, issues with delivery etc. and she managed to resolve them independently
- has experience teaching English; no experience managing others

- exercise, 1h - understood the instructions without problems, made one mistake (included a consultancy) because she didn't look at the job ad carefully enough

- asked quit a few relevant questions
- said our culture and benefits sound much better than she thought from the job ad on HH, maybe worth updating that?

- looking for 50K RUB, waiting for one offer which she expects to get this week

communication skills: high
spoken English: high
professionalism: medium
sales experience: low
leadership potential: low

Will discuss with @Anton Korenyushkin and decide how to proceed, probably worth inviting for an onsite.

@Ekaterina Bulanova we liked her - good English (both written and spoken), attitude and relevant experience. So, please make her an offer. there is the issue that she wants to relocate to the US but exactly when that will happen and whether it will happen is unclear atm, so it's a risk worth taking. cc @Anton Korenyushkin

my rough notes from the interview are below:

- company she worked for is named is hr-bot: hrmessenger.com
- worked with leads and colleagues remotely
- Jun 2020 onwards worked on new project, for English audience; found new leads via LI sales navigator - helped schedule calls
- used AmoCRM, Hubspot CRM, liked the latter because it reported on whether the lead opened the email
- doesnt like hard selling, felt like she was really helping companies she was selling to, likes that; wants to develop towards doing more bizdev
- liked that we do HR and IT, HR companies tend to treat their employees better; remote work, being paid in euros
- was given the task of presenting at unsplash 4 months into her job; because of English
- watches a lot of English language films, great spoken English, high school subjects were in English, uni in English as well
- thinks written is better than spoken
- the hardest part of the exercise was to write the sales email, 2h at most
- working hours; OK working with Moscow time zone - 2h difference
- plans to move to the US, to do a masters and to settle there, cant move right away because of COVID and because it costs money she doesnt yet have
- salary expectations; OK with starting at 400 EUR (400-600 EUR range)
- looking for remote work with international companies

text:
The Hiring Manager,

I am writing to express my interest in the business development role at Toughbyte. As a business student with a passion for sales and marketing, I am excited to leverage my skills and knowledge to help drive growth and increase revenue for your company.

Throughout my academic career, I have honed my skills in market research, strategic planning, and customer relationship management. I have also gained valuable experience through internships and part-time roles in sales and marketing, where I have developed a strong understanding of how to identify and capitalize on market opportunities, as well as build and maintain lasting relationships with clients. In addition to my academic and professional experience, I possess a strong work ethic, excellent communication skills, and the ability to work collaboratively as part of a team. I am also highly motivated and results-driven, and I thrive in a fast-paced, high-pressure environment.

I am confident that my skills and experience make me a strong candidate for the business development role at your organization. I am excited about the opportunity to contribute to your company's success, and I look forward to discussing my qualifications with you further. Thank you for considering my application
name: Viktoriya Finagenova

text:
Greetings Sir/Madam,


I hearby apply for the role of a Business Developer at Toughbyte. The position fits my interests, qualifications and experience.


I have a Degree in Finance from Kenyatta University and I am currently doing CPA Part 2. I have 7 years employment experience as a Depot Sales Manager, Assistant Regional Manager(Sales and Marketing), an asset finance officer, Marketer and Communication Assistant, Brand Ambassador and BA Supervisor for various clients across different industries, including but not limited to Oil and Gas,Automobiles, Asset Financing, Cosmetics, FMCG, and Toiletries.


I believe your company can provide me with a challenging environment while at the same time allowing me to give a hand on experience of what I've learnt through experience and from the skills I possess.


I am motivated, experienced and have an open mind to a team set up. I have proven leadership skills in various fields. I am a person with excellent communication, social and leadership skills and have therefore no problems dealing with the public and leading teams.


It's to the above effects that I promise, given the chance, to work Smart towards the achievement of your firm's goals and/or objectives. I am available to start the job immediately.


I look forward to hearing from you.


Kind regards,

Celestine Akoth Ogada.

text:
Dear Sir/Madam,

I wish to tender in my application for the position of Business Developer. I am confident my overall experience under Marketing and Business Development within various industries will make me the top candidate for this position.

My educational background is in banking and finance (bachelor of commerce degree) from the Egerton University and have since been creating and adding value for my employers and clientele for over nine years.

Over the course of my career, I have successfully undertaken extensive duties including but not limited to: Prospecting, anticipating and selling products to new and existing customers, closing sales leads within the shortest time possible and in an efficient way, conducting of market research to test the popularity of new products, arranging and distributing effectively marketing products to clientele, monitoring and evaluating competitor activity, Setting monitoring and reporting on team goals, crafting strategies for all marketing teams including digital advertising, digital communications and creative marketing, maintaining great customer service and meeting client expectations.

My work is focused on passionate, innovative and collaborative marketing strategies to meet and exceed specified targets. With regard to this position, my experience and education background is a perfect fit.

I am excited with the prospects available in your reputable organisation and will be happy to meet you to further showcase my qualification and experience. Please find the attached resume.

Yours Sincerely
Omweri Bosire Joel

text:
Dear Hiring Manager,

I am writing to express my keen interest in the position of Business Developer at Toughbyte. As an experienced business professional with a track record of success in sales and business development, I believe that my skills and expertise make me an ideal fit for this role.

Toughbyte's focus on delivering high-quality software development services that meet the needs of its clients aligns perfectly with my own career goals. I am passionate about developing strong relationships with customers, and I believe that the customer-centric approach of Toughbyte is exactly what sets it apart in the market.

I am excited by the opportunity to work with a team of talented and motivated professionals, and to use my skills to contribute to the growth and success of the company. My experience in identifying new business opportunities, managing customer relationships, and closing sales deals, would enable me to make a meaningful contribution to the business development function at Toughbyte.

Moreover, I am impressed by Toughbyte's commitment to excellence in everything it does, from software development to customer service. This resonates strongly with my own values, and I am eager to work for a company that places such a high premium on quality.

In summary, I am excited by the prospect of joining the team at Toughbyte and contributing to the growth and success of the company. Thank you for considering my application, and I look forward to the opportunity to discuss my candidacy further.

Sincerely,

Karen Kyalo.
name: Viktoriya Finagenova

I do it out of love and also the love of seeing the positive difference. I love customers a lot and I see them as people of very high value to me. text:
Dear Viktoriya,

Thank you for your email. I appreciate the opportunity to clarify my interest in the position at Toughbyte.

While the position may not be a lead or senior role, it presents a unique opportunity to work with a company that values innovation and growth. I believe that my skills and experience can contribute to Toughbytes' development and help bridge the gap between companies and developers. Additionally, I am excited about the potential for personal and professional growth within the company.

I am particularly interested in this position because I enjoy talking to people about their businesses to learn what they do and how we can improve them. I believe I can help companies and developers find each other effectively in this role.

 Additionally, I am thrilled about the possibility of remote work as I am confident in my ability to stay productive and collaborate effectively with the team in a remote environment.

I apologize for the delayed response. I was travelling the whole day.

Thank you again for considering my application. I look forward to the opportunity to discuss my qualifications further in an interview.

Best regards,

Emmanuel.
